{"ts":"2026-05-31T05:41:43.075Z","author":"claude-code-agent","op":"create","patch":[{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/id","value":"pm-qcsz"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/title","value":"Calendar: normalize recurrence exdates by instant + document count-window semantics"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/description","value":"Follow-up to pm-0l88 (timezone + all-day shipped 2026-05-31). Two secondary calendar-correctness items remain from that audit: (1) exdates are matched via exact-string Set membership (calendar.ts ~ const excluded = new Set(recurrence.exdates)), so a format mismatch (Z vs +00:00, or differing ms precision) silently fails to exclude an occurrence — normalize both exdates and candidate timestamps through Date.parse->toISOString before comparing. (2) recurrence 'count' counts occurrences from the series start_at, not from the query window start; document this window semantics in the help/contract. Low priority; no current user reports."},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/type","value":"Issue"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/status","value":"open"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/priority","value":3},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/tags","value":["calendar","correctness","recurrence"]},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/created_at","value":"2026-05-31T05:41:43.075Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/updated_at","value":"2026-05-31T05:41:43.075Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/metadata/author","value":"claude-code-agent"}],"before_hash":"3cc22dff72be7b14824654a7a64ea62b04799939b2fee54c1b5f52ca60bf6df0","after_hash":"b8bd65e0ed76042ab9a80cf5e64746017d27596715b4fdee8848dfa7b69c9f0c","message":""}
